{
  "bio": "Zach Miller is an artist based in Oklahoma City working primarily in painting, drawing, printmaking, and new media.",
  "artist_statement": [
    "The act of making is always already an act of unmaking.",
    "Through cyclical processes of creation and dissolution, my artwork carries the memory of its past forms, the same way existence is always shaped by what it has already lived and lost.",
    "Artmaking is a process of perpetual becoming, never arrival. I work to embody the sense of manifestation and the ineffable quality of experience that language can only gesture toward. I work to keep the work alive.",
    "The impossibility of fully expressing lived experience is not a failure but a productive condition — it forms the void that keeps the work moving.",
    "My work operates in the gaps between meaning and form, presence and absence, order and entropy. The world must be continuously remade or it ceases to exist.",
    "My artworks inhale and exhale. They ask not what reality is, but what it feels like to reach toward something that can never be fully held. That reaching is the work."
  ],
